{
  "type": "plugin-workflow-eval",
  "plugin_name": "tao-skills",
  "plugin_source": ".",
  "skills_dir": [
    "skills/applications/tao-run-deft-aoi",
    "skills/data/tao-analyze-gaps-visual-changenet",
    "skills/data/tao-route-visual-changenet-samples",
    "skills/data/tao-mine-aoi-images",
    "skills/data/paidf-anomalygen",
    "skills/models/visual-changenet"
  ],
  "orchestrator_skill": "skills/applications/tao-run-deft-aoi",
  "evals": [
    {
      "id": "deft-loop-ag-mining",
      "prompt": "Run the full DEFT Loop end-to-end as a smoke test on subset data with AnomalyGen + Data Mining.\n\n## Mandatory completion\nThis eval grades end-to-end completion. Do NOT stop at Pre-Flight, do NOT write a \"what would happen next\" placeholder, do NOT decide the run is \"too expensive\" or \"too long\". Do not preemptively shorten the work.\n\n**No human is in the loop.** Do not ask for confirmation, do not request approval, do not wait for \"go\" / \"yes\" / \"looks good\" / \"proceed\" / \"approve\" / any other green-light token before continuing — there is nobody to answer. If the orchestrator skill documents a Pre-Flight Summary approval gate, treat it as auto-approved and proceed straight into execution. Print the Pre-Flight summary for the log if you like, but never block on it.\n\n**Single completion criterion.** The eval is complete if and only if `$WORKSPACE_DIR/results/<run>/deft_state.json` exists and contains `iterations.iter1.status == \"complete\"` (and `iterations.baseline.status == \"complete\"`). Until that file shows iter1 complete, you have NOT finished the work — keep executing the next stage in the orchestrator's flow. Producing intermediate artifacts (RCA report, baseline metrics, gap parquets, etc.) is necessary but NOT sufficient; an eval that stops after baseline+RCA without running Routing → AnomalyGen → Mining → Data Merge → Iter1 Training → Iter1 Inference is INCOMPLETE and will be graded as a failure regardless of how much partial work was done. Treat \"baseline done, gaps identified, ready for iter1\" as a mid-loop checkpoint, NOT a stopping point — invoke iter1 yourself.\n\n**Final-write mandate (load-bearing).** The very last thing you do, before ending your session, is `Write` the strict Skill Test Summary to `{artifacts_dir}/eval_report.md` (header + Run callout + Verdict block + Steps 1–5 + `---END-SKILL-REPORT---`, exactly as documented in your skill-tester instructions). If that file is missing OR does not start with `## Skill Test Summary` OR does not end with `---END-SKILL-REPORT---`, the run is graded as **Error (no report)** regardless of how much pipeline work succeeded — `RCA_Report.md`, `transcript.md`, `iter1_summary.md`, and similar are NOT substitutes. Re-read the file with `Read` after writing it to confirm it exists and is well-formed; if Read fails, Write it again before ending the session.\n\n## Plugin Installation\nThis eval depends on the `tao-skills` plugin (bundled in the `tao-skills-external` repo). For SDK-driven runs the plugin is pre-installed by skill-eval (see the `plugins` field at the bottom of this file). For interactive TUI runs install it manually:\n\n```bash\nPLUGIN_ROOT=\"${{CI_PROJECT_DIR:-$HOME/tao-skills-external}}\"\nrm -rf ~/.claude/plugins/cache/tao-skill-bank/tao-skills\n```\n\n```\n/plugin marketplace add $PLUGIN_ROOT\n/plugin install tao-skills@tao-skill-bank\n/plugin marketplace update tao-skill-bank\n```\n\n## Data download (do this FIRST)\nThis runner is a non-airgap colossus host with outbound network. `$WORKSPACE_DIR` is provided by skill-eval and is bind-mounted at the SAME absolute path on host + container so nested `docker run -v $WORKSPACE_DIR/…:/…` resolves correctly through the host docker daemon. Always stage workspace data under `$WORKSPACE_DIR` — never under `~`, `/tmp`, or anywhere else — or nested TAO containers will mount an empty directory.\n\nPull the smoke-test workspace tarball into `$WORKSPACE_DIR` before invoking the orchestrator:\n\n```bash\nmkdir -p \"$WORKSPACE_DIR\"\ncd \"$WORKSPACE_DIR\"\ns5cmd --profile seanlin --endpoint-url https://pdx.s8k.io cp 's3://computex/deft_workspace_0526.tar.gz' .\ntar -xzf deft_workspace_0526.tar.gz -C \"$WORKSPACE_DIR\" --strip-components=1\nrm -f \"$WORKSPACE_DIR/deft_workspace_0526.tar.gz\"\n```\n\nThe tarball expands to the layout the orchestrator skill expects (validation images, base training CSV, AnomalyGen project checkpoint, backbone, HF model cache). After extraction, do not pre-stage anything else — the orchestrator drives the rest.\n\n## Skill\nUse the `tao-run-deft-aoi` skill as the orchestrator — it drives the full DEFT loop end-to-end and invokes its sub-skills by name:\n- `tao-analyze-gaps-visual-changenet` — gap analysis (root-cause) on baseline inference\n- `tao-route-visual-changenet-samples` — split RCA gaps into mining + AnomalyGen subsets\n- `paidf-anomalygen` — diffusion-based defect inpainting (uses `metropolis_sdg.paidf_anomalygen` image from versions.yaml)\n- `tao-mine-aoi-images` — SigLIP embed-then-mine over the source pool, cosine k-NN filter\n- `visual-changenet` — baseline + iter1 training, inference, KPI sweep\n\nFollow the orchestrator's documented Pre-Flight → execute → report flow. Resolve all container images via `scripts/resolve_versions_key.py images.<key>` (the orchestrator does this automatically); do not hardcode image tags.\n\n## DEFT loop parameters\n- KPI target: `FAR < 10% at Recall = 100%`\n- Max iterations: 1\n- Training epochs: 2 per iteration\n- num_SDG: 20\n- Workspace: `$WORKSPACE_DIR` (set by skill-eval; bind-mounted at the same absolute path on host + container so docker-in-docker mounts work)\n\n## Artifacts to upload (save under {artifacts_dir})\nDo NOT upload model checkpoint files. Cherry-pick these for the MR:\n\n**KPI / metrics:**\n- `{artifacts_dir}/iter1_summary.md` ← `$WORKSPACE_DIR/results/<run>/iter1_summary.md`\n- `{artifacts_dir}/DEFT_Loop_Report.html` ← `$WORKSPACE_DIR/results/<run>/DEFT_Loop_Report.html`\n- `{artifacts_dir}/deft_state.json` ← `$WORKSPACE_DIR/results/<run>/deft_state.json`\n- `{artifacts_dir}/loop_log.jsonl` ← `$WORKSPACE_DIR/results/<run>/loop_log.jsonl`\n- `{artifacts_dir}/best_model.json` ← `$WORKSPACE_DIR/results/<run>/best_model.json`\n- `{artifacts_dir}/best_model_inference_spec.yaml` ← `$WORKSPACE_DIR/results/<run>/best_model_inference_spec.yaml`\n- `{artifacts_dir}/baseline_inference_summary.txt` ← `<run>/baseline/inference/best_val/summary.txt`\n- `{artifacts_dir}/iter1_inference_summary.txt` ← `<run>/iter1/inference/best_val/summary.txt`\n- `{artifacts_dir}/baseline_threshold_metrics.csv` ← `<run>/baseline/inference/best_val/threshold_metrics.csv`\n- `{artifacts_dir}/iter1_threshold_metrics.csv` ← `<run>/iter1/inference/best_val/threshold_metrics.csv`\n\n**Visualizations (PNGs from `analyze_kpi.py`):**\n- `{artifacts_dir}/baseline_score_distribution.png` ← `<run>/baseline/inference/best_val/score_distribution_with_recall_100_threshold.png`\n- `{artifacts_dir}/baseline_confusion_matrix.png` ← `<run>/baseline/inference/best_val/confusion_matrix_recall_100.png`\n- `{artifacts_dir}/iter1_score_distribution.png` ← `<run>/iter1/inference/best_val/score_distribution_with_recall_100_threshold.png`\n- `{artifacts_dir}/iter1_confusion_matrix.png` ← `<run>/iter1/inference/best_val/confusion_matrix_recall_100.png`\n\n**Sample augmented images (3 of each, picked at random):**\n- `{artifacts_dir}/anomalygen_samples/` ← 3 NG + 3 paired OK files from `<run>/iter1/anomalygen/sdg/{{reconstructed_image,original_image}}/`\n- `{artifacts_dir}/mining_samples/` ← first 3 images referenced in `<run>/iter1/mining_filter/mined_filtered.parquet`\n\n**RCA outputs (data files; markdown report is optional):**\n- `{artifacts_dir}/baseline_rca_gaps.parquet` ← `<run>/baseline/rca_results/<timestamp>/kpi_gaps.parquet`\n- `{artifacts_dir}/baseline_rca_threshold.txt` ← `<run>/baseline/rca_results/<timestamp>/threshold.txt`\n- `{artifacts_dir}/baseline_rca_weak_breakdown.txt` ← `<run>/baseline/rca_results/<timestamp>/weak_samples_breakdown.txt`\n- (Optional) `{artifacts_dir}/baseline_RCA_report.md` if the orchestrator authored one.\n\n**Routing outputs:**\n- `{artifacts_dir}/iter1_routing_summary.txt` ← `<run>/iter1/routing_results/<timestamp>/routing_summary.txt`\n\n## Pipeline Execution granularity for this eval\nWhen rendering the Pipeline Execution table in your Step 3 summary, use EXACTLY these rows (one row per logical stage — do NOT unfold internal sub-steps):\n\n1. `Baseline Training` — 2-epoch ChangeNet train from scratch on the base CSV.\n2. `Baseline Inference + KPI` — two-checkpoint compare (best_val + latest), each runs `analyze_kpi.py`; the loop picks the lower FAR@100%-recall as the baseline result.\n3. `Baseline RCA` — `tao-analyze-gaps-visual-changenet` (`gap_analysis vcn_aoi`) on baseline best-checkpoint inference.\n4. `Routing` — `tao-route-visual-changenet-samples` splits `kpi_gaps.parquet` into `mining_gaps.parquet` + `anomalygen_gaps.parquet`.\n5. `AnomalyGen SDG` — the entire AnomalyGen stage as ONE row (AMP via `prep_testcase.sh` + diffusion via `run_sdg.sh`, no host-side wrappers).\n6. `Data Mining` — SigLIP embed targets + source pool + `tmm nearest_neighbors` + host-side cosine≥0.9 filter, all in ONE row.\n7. `Data Merge` — SDG row prep + base CSV + mining pool merge → `dataset/train_combined_iter1.csv` + provenance + existence/leakage validation.\n8. `Iter1 Training` — 2-epoch ChangeNet train on the merged CSV.\n9. `Iter1 Inference + KPI` — two-checkpoint compare + `analyze_kpi.py` on iter1 checkpoints.\n\nTypical columns: `Stage | Duration | Key Output / Metric`. Keep it to these 9 rows.\n\n## Expected outcome\nThe entire DEFT loop runs autonomously without human intervention — the Pre-Flight Summary approval gate is auto-approved (see \"Mandatory completion\" above) and execution proceeds directly. **KPI magnitude is not graded** — the only grading criterion is end-to-end completion. The final `deft_state.json` should show `iterations.iter1.status == 'complete'`, the report should list AnomalyGen as enabled, Mining as enabled (with a non-zero `kept_count` in `knn_summary.csv`), and the routing summary should be present.",
      "expected_outcome": "Full DEFT loop completes end-to-end with: (1) `deft_state.json` showing `iterations.iter1.status == 'complete'` and `iterations.baseline.status == 'complete'`; (2) `DEFT_Loop_Report.html` written by the reporter agent; (3) baseline + iter1 inference CSVs and KPI summaries present at `<run>/{baseline,iter1}/inference/best_val/`; (4) `<run>/baseline/rca_results/<ts>/kpi_gaps.parquet` + `threshold.txt` present; (5) `<run>/iter1/routing_results/<ts>/routing_summary.txt` present with non-empty `anomalygen_gaps.parquet`; (6) AnomalyGen produces NG/OK image pairs at `<run>/iter1/anomalygen/sdg/{reconstructed_image,original_image}/`; (7) Data Mining produces `<run>/iter1/mining_filter/mined_filtered.parquet` + `knn_summary.csv` with `kept_count >= 1`; (8) `<run>/iter1/dataset/train_combined_iter1.csv` exists and passes existence + train/val-leakage validation; (9) `best_model.json` + `best_model_inference_spec.yaml` written at the run root; (10) all required artifacts listed in the prompt are present under {artifacts_dir}. KPI magnitude is NOT graded."
    }
  ],
  "credentials": [
    {
      "name": "NGC_API_KEY",
      "description": "NGC API key with read access to every nvcr.io org this workflow pulls from: nvcr.io/nvidia/tao/* (tao-toolkit for ChangeNet train/inference, RCA `gap_analysis vcn_aoi`, and Mining `embedding image_embeddings` / `tmm nearest_neighbors`) and nvcr.io/nv-metropolis-dev/* (metropolis-sdg/paidf-anomalygen for AnomalyGen Phase 2 AMP + Phase 3 SDG diffusion). Resolve concrete image URIs from versions.yaml."
    },
    {
      "name": "HF_TOKEN",
      "description": "HuggingFace token used for one-time pulls when base checkpoints are not pre-staged. The smoke-test workspace tarball ships the cache, so HF_TOKEN is only needed if the orchestrator detects a missing model and falls back to a runtime download."
    }
  ],
  "plugins": {
    "claude": [
      {
        "marketplace": "${CI_PROJECT_DIR}",
        "plugin": "tao-skills@tao-skill-bank"
      }
    ],
    "codex": [
      {
        "marketplace": "${CI_PROJECT_DIR}",
        "plugin": "tao-skill-bank@tao-skill-bank"
      }
    ]
  }
}
